d weather you may have to find alternate parking farther away  Notices will be posted on the VMI website with further information  Shuttle service will run continuously from Moody Hall to Cameron Hall beginning at 0800 a m  until 11 00 a m The shuttles will resume following the ceremony    The doors to Cameron Hall will open at 0930 Please arrive in time to be seated by 1045 Seating is on a first come  first served basis  Due to limited seating  no one will be admitted without a ticket  Due to space constraints and security reasons  coolers  backpacks and baskets are not allowed at any commencement ceremony location  Strollers must be able to be folded and out of the aisles  All carry in items are subject to search at the door  Wheelchair seating is available  Handicap drop off is located in front of Cameron Hall  Please email the Chief of Staff s Office at chiefofstaff vmi edu if you have certain handicap seating needs    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 